title: Guadalupe Silerio
data: María Guadalupe Silerio Núñez (born 12 December 1971) is a Mexican politician from the Party of the Democratic Revolution. From 2009 to 2010 she served as Deputy of the LXI Legislature of the Mexican Congress representing Durango.[1] This article about a Party of the Democratic Revolution politician is a stub.
